My idea of community is that people all put into it what they get out of it.  If you are only interested in yourself, than I'm sure you would see it that way.  But it is much more than that I believe antonelf.  I think that people share common goals and hopes for their respective communities, and I would think that would be the prosperity of all those who live within it.  However I think you take a quite pessimistic view of that idea, insisting that everyone else will take advantage of yours and others' generousity.  I can't make you share my viewpoint, and you probably can't make me share yours, but we can at least agree that there are two different views on the issue.
