Before I start I'd like to point out something... (I am likely to be wrong on the numbers but bear with me) There are 30 or so Million people in Canada and nearly 300 million in the USA. Yes, Meletus in large urban centers, There is no sense of community. At no time does the City, County or State look out for my best interests. They tax me and they put in amenitys to attract taxpayers to their City, County and State. Beyond that only people make a community and very few make any effort to make life easier. They may hold social events, benefits and other such activities but at the end of the day they have contributed NOTHING to make my life easier. 
<br />

<br />
In a small rural community as you are more likely used to, there is a sense of community of fair play and of community betterment. But the larger a community grows, the more ethnicly diverse, the less in common these people have and the more divergent their points of view. 
<br />

<br />
In places like NYC, LA and Newark the sense of community is long gone. Hell some people cant even relate to each other due to language, culture, social class or income level.
<br />

<br />
