You must be missing the crux of the argument for nationalized health care.  The basic premise behind it is that EVERYONE uses the system in their lives.  Less when you are young, more when you are old.  I'm sure some people use it more than others, but everyone does use it.  And everyone pays for it.  Makes sense to me, I just dont get how you can't see it that way.
<br />

