				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Without insult Zerg, Everyone CANT pay for it... Some dont work, some got here last week... some never did work. 
<br />

<br />
X number of people cant afford to pay for health care and Y number of people cant afford not to have healthcare. 
<br />

<br />
X&lt;Y but &lt; The total of numbers of people that pay for health care.
<br />

<br />
With X+Y= less than the total, the equation still comes out to be total - (X+Y)
<br />

<br />
There for Intuitively We SHOULD KNOW that not only cant there be complete health care coverage for everyone, but subtract X &amp; Y from the equation... Total = -(X+Y). 
<br />
 
