			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Addressing Antonelf's initial post, and the post's title of "Should we just hand the country over to New Englanders?":
<br />

<br />
I think what it comes down to, is if you look at statistical information between say, the south and the northeast (especially New England) you find that the north (New England in particular) is able to better care for itself in most every way. I'm not sure why this is. I'm not sure if it's an old Mason-Dixon line issue that's always been there, or because the north was settled first and is smaller, or if there's just normal expected economic reasons that will never really go away. I just know that, from experience, and based on all the data I can find, it's true.
<br />

<br />
Here's some statistical data on credit ratings of certain cities. According to this, the majority of cities that score below the average of 678 are in the south:
<br />
<a href="http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/Banking/Yourcreditrating/P80782.asp" target="_blank">http://moneycentral.msn.com/content/Banking/Yourcreditrating/P80782.asp</a>
<br />

<br />
Statistical information on the healthiest states. The states that rank the lowest are, in majority, the south:
<br />
<a href="http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/4759503/" target="_blank">http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/4759503/</a>
<br />

<br />
There's a lot of factors that contribute to this. It's a problem that deserves more attention in my opinion, but it's not a pride shot, or a "we're better than you". The people in the south aren't stupid, and the people in the north or New England aren't smarter. It seems to be more a function of the culture, geography, and how the economies of those areas structured (what they create, what they need).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://webster.ij.net/~eop/sigs/bichoasig_sm.gif" border="0" /></a>
<br />
[<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31004" target="_blank" class="postlink">66 Arcanist</a>] Bicrius Nebulous &lt;<a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a>&gt;
<br />
<a href="http://eqluclin.com/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Luclin Server</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
